{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/transient-ischaemic-attacks-and-driving.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/transient-ischaemic-attacks-and-driving","title":"Transient ischaemic attack (TIA) and driving","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:17:19+00:00","details":{"need_id":"2426","business_proposition":false,"description":"You may need to tell DVLA if you've had a transient ischaemic attack (TIA) - download the correct form if you need to let them know","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>You may need to tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> if you have had a transient ischaemic attack (<abbr title=\"Transient ischaemic attack\">TIA</abbr>) - also known as a ‘mini-stroke’.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Car or motorcycle licence</h2>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need to tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, download leaflet &lsquo;TIA1 - Car or motorcycle drivers who have had a stroke or transient ischaemic attack&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@motor/documents/digitalasset/dg_067958.pdf\" title=\"Download 'TIA1 - Car or motorcycle drivers who have had a stroke or transient ischaemic attack' (PDF, 260KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘TIA1 - Car or motorcycle drivers who have had a stroke or transient ischaemic attack’ (PDF, 260KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Bus, coach or lorry licence</h2>\n\n<p>You must tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr>. Fill in form STR1V and send it to the address on the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@motor/documents/digitalasset/dg_201618.pdf\" title=\"Download medical questionnaire\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘STR1V - Confidential medical information’ (PDF, 315KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":"Mini-stroke and driving"},"tags":[],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/driving-if-disabled.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-if-disabled","title":"Medical conditions, disabilities and driving","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-11-14T12:25:08+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/health-conditions-and-driving.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/health-conditions-and-driving","title":"Health conditions and driving","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:25:48+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/giving-up-your-driving-licence.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/giving-up-your-driving-licence","title":"Surrendering your driving licence","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-11-14T12:45:33+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/reapply-driving-licence-medical-condition.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/reapply-driving-licence-medical-condition","title":"Re-apply for a driving licence following a medical condition","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-11-30T12:27:11+00:00"}]}